The design of C++11 started way before 2011, hence articles from 2008.<p><pre><code>  get_pointer() = 1;
</code></pre>
assigning 1 to a pointer isn&#x27;t the best idea :P so I think you mean you read<p><pre><code>  int& get_reference();
  get_reference() = 1;
</code></pre>
which is about <i>lvalue references</i>, not <i>rvalue references</i>, and has existed in C++ since the beginning.
